Problem Statement : Imagine a chess board of size 10 X 10. I am moving an object at 2 X 2 such that it must pass through all the cells of the chessboard starting at (0, 0) which is the bottom left corner of the board. Therefore, the object will start from (2, 2), then traverse to (0, 0) then to (0, 1), (0, 2) .... (0, 9) , (1, 0), .....(9, 9)

Issue being observed : The object doesn't pass through all the cells; it takes a short cut and moves along the diagonal like starting (2, 2) through (9, 9). Why is this happening? Any thoughts or is it a bug in the implementation somewhere and an issue must be opened?

Note : I have verified the position of each of the cells in the chess board for correctness. I am not making any mistake in those. 

